ma: a film to celebrate 100 years of cinema: by Stanley Kwan", "work_id": 87466, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "09 OCT 1957", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 290, "name": "People's Republic of China", "slug": "peoples-republic-of-china"}], "biography": "Stanley Kwan (traditional Chinese: 關錦鵬; simplified Chinese: 关锦鹏); born 9 October 1957) is a Hong Kong film director and producer.\n\nKwan landed a job at TVB after receiving a mass communications degree at Hong Kong Baptist College. Kwan's first film was Women (1985), which starred Chow Yun-fat, and was a big box-office success.\n\nKwan's films often deal sympathetically with the plight of women and their struggles with romantic affairs of the heart.  Rouge (1987), Full Moon in New York (1989), Center Stage (1992; a.k.a. Actress), a biopic on silent film star Ruan Lingyu and Everlasting Regret (2005), are all such typical Kwan films. Red Rose White Rose (1994) is an adaptation of an Eileen Chang novel. The film was entered into the 45th Berlin International Film Festival. His 1998 film Hold You Tight won the Alfred Bauer Prize and Teddy Award at the 48th Berlin International Film Festival.Kwan came out as a gay man in 1996 in Yang ± Yin, his documentary looking at the history of Chinese-language film through the prism of gender roles and sexuality. He is one of the few openly gay directors in Asia and one of the very few to have worked on these themes. His Lan Yu (2001) adapts a gay love story originally published on the Internet.\n\nKwan is also an occasional lecturer at the City University of Hong Kong, where he teaches directing and writing to students. Source: Wikidata; 01/08/2023", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-14T20:27:45.790433+11:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5191, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stanley_Kwan"}], "uuid": "5aeb6a25-d8e4-49cf-8e31-5e48036b0191", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "28969", "external_references": [{"id": 26388, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q705995"}, {"id": 31601, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "71035398"}, {"id": 31602, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no2001009087"}, {"id": 31603, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no2001009087"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-14T20:27:45.790672+11:00"}, {"id": 29475, "name": "Media Asia Distribution", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2794738, "title": "Yang and yin: gender in Chinese cinema: a film to celebrate 100 years of cinema: by Stanley Kwan", "work_id": 87466, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2138543, "title": "City on fire", "work_id": 87637, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T19:33:44.206017+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "e8a38bdf-325f-4d25-aca9-d37a97f90883", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "10407", "external_references": [], "date_modified": "2025-03-14T20:27:44.609942+11:00"}, {"id": 29473, "name": "Pierre-Olivier Bardet", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2327946, "title": "The Art of piano", "work_id": 88801, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1997904, "title": "Madame Butterfly [Widescreen]", "work_id": 93537, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1817726, "title": "Yehudi Menuhin: the violin of the century", "work_id": 87464, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "dat